It is an inside look into the Hip Hop video industry.  A must have if you are curious about what goes on behind the curtains!  It's not a pro-Karrine Steffans at all although it is very fair in balancing the point of view of the video vixen.  Lots of sex going on and Wendy Williams should give up her day job and narrate docs!  The title sequence is halarious.  The DVD extras are great as well and unless you are a total prude you'll really enjoy this.

The only reason I gave this movie any stars because it gives a peak into the world of hip hop. It was degrading and disrespectful only because Karrine wasn't in the documentary to give he raise of each story. Very one sided, like an attack. The documentary was entertaining and informative, I just wish she had a POV as well. I probably won't watch this or another doc like this again.
